cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with the computation of a filtration of nested cell complexes for the offsets of convex objects, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves topological analysis, which suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as another possible sub-category. The use of Voronoi diagrams and analysis of their size and complexity suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as additional sub-categories. Finally, the mention of experiments involving input approximation suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as a possible sub-category.
